gomodel:SYNGO_59  a       owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Rab3C specific antibody was used to probe highly purified synaptic vesicles obtained by subcellular fractionation and CPG chromatography, revealing the enrichment of Rab3C on these vesicles.\n\n19/01/2017 Pim\nThe *anchored\" element in the annotation comes from figure 4 where dissociation from the SV is shown (is not integral) and the known lipid anchor of Rab proteins (including Rab3C).\n\nUniprot: Lipidation: S-geranylgeranyl cysteine. Experimental description: Figure legend \" Synaptosomes were prepared from rat cerebral\ncortex by differential centrifugation and subsequently lysed by osmotic\nshock.\"" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0098993 replaced by GO:0030672" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5615-1014" ;
